<TITLE> Aftab ruled out of tri-nation series and Asia Cup </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com) Aftab Ahmed has been ruled out of this month's tri-nation one-day international series following a finger injury. Aftab will also miss the 2008 Asia Cup, scheduled for June 24-July 6 in Pakistan. The tri-nation involving India, Pakistan and hosts Bangladesh are scheduled for June 8-14 at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium in Mirpur. The selectors has called middle order batsman Alok Kapali for both series in place of Aftab Ahmed, who has been advised rest for around six weeks, Bangladesh Cricket Board said in a statement Sunday. Aftab was stuck by a ball while batting in practice on Saturday which resulted in a dislocation and bone fracture in his finger. X-ray confirmed the fracture, which requires surgical repair. About the inclusion of Alok, chief selector Rafiqul Alam said that they considered Alok's experience to replace Aftab. bd
